aces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"7cdb4b6d758d633034ff1c1f4f070c5fe95c8aac","tid":862221,"uid":60398,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-14T17:07:09.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>唔想潑冷水，但清醒少少，揾個神父出黎，好可能係因為美國官方唔想見打正旗號要港獨既人；<br />\n<br />\n美國關係法寫明承認中國主權<br />\n<br />\n所以官方會避免正式接見<br />\n<br />\n但同時，香港似乎有n樣野違反咗關係法或其前設，不合美國利益（以及香港長遠利益）<br />\n<br />\n所以，無論同咩人表達訴求，諗清楚先講訴求乜野<br />\n<br />\n唔係因為想美國支持香港人乜乜乜所以做野<br />\n<br />\n而係因為香港有違反關係法既情況，香港民主自由etc,所以<strong><ins>不<ins>合美國利益</ins></ins></strong>，所以希望美國做野<br />\n<br />\nFYI:<br />\n<br />\nThe Congress makes the following findings and declarations:<br />\n<br />\n(1) The Congress recognizes that under the 1984 Sino-British Joint Declaration:<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">(A) The People's Republic of China and the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland have agreed that the People's Republic of China will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1, 1997</span>. Until that time, the United Kingdom will be responsible for the administration of Hong Kong.<br />\n<br />\n(B) The Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China, beginning on July 1, 1997, will continue to enjoy a high degree of autonomy on all matters other than defense and foreign affairs.<br />\n<br />\n⋯⋯<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">(5) Support for democratization is a fundamental principle of United States foreign policy. As such, it naturally applies to United States policy toward Hong Kong. This will remain equally true after June 30, 1997.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">(6) The human rights of the people of Hong Kong are of great importance to the United States and are directly relevant to United States interests in Hong Kong. </span>A fully successful transition in the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong must safeguard human rights in and of themselves. Human rights also serve as a basis for Hong Kong's continued economic prosperity.<br />\n<br />\n⋯</blockquote><br />\nfrom 通街都係處 巴打<br />\n突發。美國牧師bob到美領撐港獨聯<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/fyRFrNX\" target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/fyRFrNX</a><br />\n#228 回覆 - 分享自 LIHKG 討論區</blockquote>"},{"pid":"1d4d8f9614456c0ae32e1fcebc5cf4b10dae3652","tid":862221,"uid":776,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-14T17:09:02.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"c69753cb9316744792a51fa00699fa229a0b13bc","tid":862221,"uid":40448,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"quote":{"pid":"661c84b53805068b168eb17ee9236ca705d21d81","tid":862221,"uid":179645,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"75c2ba28e4b51e9598f617675593c54cf82f3e24","tid":862221,"uid":40448,"like":10,"dislike":2,"score":8,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-10-14T16:40:26.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dislike.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2018-10-14T16:58:25.000Z","msg":"可唔可以幫幫手轉英文<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n香港政府有計劃以現時國際特殊地位響個方面去支援支那同美國打經濟戰. 提議美國盡快通過美國香港人權民主法, 凍結香港政策法以保護美國利益"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-10-14T17:09:55.000Z","msg":"The Hong Kong Government is trying to capitalize on the city&rsquo;s unique role in international trade and relationship to favor Communist China&rsquo;s effort in the current heated trade dispute against USA. America, please stand up for equality and justice to pass Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act in the Congress to establishes punitive measures against government officials in Hong Kong or mainland China who are responsible for suppressing basic freedoms in Hong Kong."},{"pid":"e1367ae4874aedd3d16c08781772c9e2fd121c4d","tid":862221,"uid":40448,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"02e7b440f0c0631a3847d2cf0d3befa399098543","tid":862221,"uid":60398,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quot